import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import seaborn as sns 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
user_agent = 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/116.0.0.0 Safari/537.36'
url = 'https://www.imdb.com/chart/top/' #The IMDB url that contains top 250 ranked movies
response = requests.get(url,headers = {'User-Agent':user_agent,'Accept-Language' : 'en-US,en;q=0.5'})    #get request
print(response)

# passing response object into BeautifulSoup constructor to parse the document
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content,'html.parser')
# Passing the tag that contains our required data into BeatifulSoup object
movie_data = soup.findAll('li',attrs={'class' : 'ipc-metadata-list-summary-item sc-59b6048d-0 jemTre cli-parent'})
movie_rank = []
movie_name = []
released_year = []
duration = []
rated_type = []
ratings = []
votes = []

# To convert votes count from Millions and thousands to numbers
def convert_votes_to_int (vote):
    if 'M' in vote:
        return int(float(vote.replace('M','')) * 1000000)
    elif 'K' in vote:
        return int(float(vote.replace('K','')) * 1000)
    else:
        return int(vote)
    
# Convert duration into minutes
def convert_to_minutes(r_time):
    total_minutes = 0

    parts = r_time.split()
    for part in parts:
        if 'h' in part:
            total_minutes += int(part.replace('h','')) * 60
        elif 'm' in part:
            total_minutes += int(part.replace('m',''))
    return total_minutes

    
for movie in movie_data:
    #  Name and rank
    rank_name = movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__c").div.a.text
    rank = int(rank_name.split('. ')[0])
    name = rank_name.split('. ')[1]
    movie_rank.append(rank)
    movie_name.append(name)

    # year
    year = int(movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__c").find('span').find_next('span').text)
    released_year.append(year)

    # Duration of movie
    runtime = movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__c").findAll('span')[2].text
    runtime = convert_to_minutes(runtime)
    duration.append(runtime)

    # Rated Type
    r_type = movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__tc").find('span').find_next('span').find_next('span').find_next('span').text
    rated_type.append(r_type)

    # Ratings
    rating = movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__c").find('span',class_='ipc-rating-star ipc-rating-star--base ipc-rating-star--imdb ratingGroup--imdb-rating').text.split('(')[0]
    rating = float(rating)
    ratings.append(rating)

    # votes
    vote = movie.find('div',class_="ipc-metadata-list-summary-item__c").find('span',class_='ipc-rating-star ipc-rating-star--base ipc-rating-star--imdb ratingGroup--imdb-rating').find_next('span').text
    vote = vote.replace('(','').replace(')','')
    vote = convert_votes_to_int(vote)
    votes.append(vote)
    
df = pd.DataFrame({'Rank' : movie_rank, 'Movie_Name' : movie_name,'Duration(Minutes)' : duration, 'Released_Year' : released_year,'Certification' : rated_type,'Ratings' : ratings,'Votes' : votes})
df.head(10)

ratings_certification.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, colormap='viridis', figsize=(12, 8))
plt.title('Distribution of Ratings by Certification')
plt.xlabel('Certification')
plt.ylabel('Number of Movies')
plt.legend(title='IMDb Rating')
plt.show()
